[Japanese encephalitis virus infections are suspected in all of these cases. The monsoon has begun, which signals the beginning of the JE virus transmission season. Laboratory tests confirmed JE virus infection in 4 of the patients and the status of the remaining patients awaits laboratory confirmation. The report above does not provide information about the vaccination status of the affected individuals or of the population in the area where they live.

A map of India can be seen at http://www.mapsofindia.com/images2/india-map.jpg. A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map showing the location of Arunachal Pradesh state in far north eastern India can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2638359,298. - Mod.TY]
